      "writtenOn": "2018-01-10T16:27:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I know that Breakpad does some pretty weird handling here. Does it do this?\n\nUltimately, I think we’ll want to invent a new “CodeView” record type (not really CodeView, but something to use in the place of the 7.0 PDB link in minidumps) that just carries the full NT_GNU_BUILD_ID, however long it was. But for now, for compatibility with existing Breakpad symbols, we’ve kind of got to play along…",
      "revId": "b7f2f06b2e687be192b151869807bb887292569b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
