    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9815f932_4bde4567",
        "filename": "snapshot/linux/module_snapshot_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 141,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-01-10T19:26:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The Breakpad client returns the whole build-id (https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/third_party/breakpad/breakpad/src/common/linux/file_id.cc?rcl\u003d4a02ec03038d9d6f870f42d5070591512f488db0\u0026l\u003d87)\nwhich the processor then trims or pads into an MDGUID (https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/third_party/breakpad/breakpad/src/processor/minidump.cc?rcl\u003d4a02ec03038d9d6f870f42d5070591512f488db0\u0026l\u003d2153).\n\nThe client also falls back to hashing the start of the .text section which I don\u0027t think we can reliably find. (https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/third_party/breakpad/breakpad/src/common/linux/file_id.cc?rcl\u003d4a02ec03038d9d6f870f42d5070591512f488db0\u0026l\u003d121)",
